{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Revoke the BBC Royal Charter, abolish the TV Licence Fee & privatise the BBC",
        "additional_details": "We believe the BBC is no longer the trusted \u2018backbone\u2019 of Britain it once was, having been linked to multiple scandals and alleged cover-ups. This has driven boycotts and reduced willingness to pay the TV Licence amongst many, alongside the rise of cheaper, better streaming alternatives. In a digital, data-driven era, we feel government control of the airwaves to curb disinformation is outdated. Moreover, we believe it seems unjust that a licence is required for all live broadcasts when only the BBC is funded by the fee.",
        "background": "Abolish the mandatory TV licence fee and revoke the BBC\u2019s Royal Charter. Legislate to transition the BBC into a private corporation, as they did with BBC Studio's. We believe the BBC should compete independently in the media market without state funding & Royal Charter rights, akin to BBC Studios.",
